node_modules/
.env
.orche/
*.log

# harness transient runtime state (manifest.json is intentionally tracked)
.harness/lock
.harness/txn/
.harness/session-*

# This repo commits EXACTLY ONE lockfile: pnpm-lock.yaml (packageManager is
# pnpm@*, CI uses pnpm/action-setup, `harness bootstrap` uses pnpm). The orche
# release gate picks its frozen install command from whichever root lockfile it
# finds, in the order bun.lock -> pnpm-lock.yaml -> `npm ci`, so ANY other root
# lockfile hijacks the gate and runs a package manager nobody here maintains.
# That is META-HARNESS-98: a stale bun.lock made the gate run
# `bun install --frozen-lockfile`, which failed on package.json drift and
# blocked the dev -> main promotion. Keep stray lockfiles out of the tree;
# test/lockfile-toolchain.test.ts enforces the same invariant.
bun.lock
# Also inert-but-kept: with a known lockfile present the gate always takes the
# frozen path and never runs the tree-mutating portable `npm install` that
# synthesizes a package-lock.json — but an untracked one would trip the gate's
# treeClean promotion guard, so belt-and-braces. Never commit it.
package-lock.json
